l. Indeed, our data require a steeper relation\nbetween L_X, L_K, and sigma_e than predicted by standard mass-loss models.\nFinally, we find a statistically significant correlation between sigma_e and\nT_gas, suggesting that T_gas is set by the galaxy potential inside the optical\neffective radius. We conclude that within the inner-most 10-30kpc region,\nearly-types maintain pressure-supported hot gas, with a minimum T_gas set by\nthe virial temperature, but the majority show evidence for some additional\nheating.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Apr 2016 20:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 26 Jul 2016 18:48:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-17"}
