er, (multi-) thermal energy estimated employing low-energy band of\nthe SXR spectrum result in higher values than that derived from the\ncombined-energy band. On the contrary, the analysis of high-energy band of SXR\nspectrum lead to lower thermal energy than that estimated from the\ncombined-energy band.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Apr 2016 09:36:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-08"}
